New Records: Ruben Trumpelmann became the first bowler in men's T20I to pick up two wickets in the first two balls of the match.
Trumpelmann registered his career-best figures of four for 21.
Trumpelmann's figures of 4 for 21 were also the best for Namibia in a T20 World Cup match.
Key Match Events: Ruben Trumpelmann took four for 21 as Oman were bowled out for 109 in 19.4 overs.
Trumpelmann got the big wickets of opener Kashyap Prajapati and captain Aqib Ilyas in the first two deliveries of the game.
Trumpelmann removed wicketkeeper Naseem Khushi for 6 in his second over.
Trumpelmann got tail-ender Kaleemullah in the 19th over of the innings.
David Wiese chipped in with three wickets.
Captain Gerhard Erasmus took two wickets and conceded just 20 runs in four overs.
Pre-Game Insights: Captain Gerhard Erasmus won the toss and opted to bowl on a pitch that had plenty of assistance for bowlers.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Oman never got going in their innings as they kept losing wickets at regular intervals.
Zeeshan Maqsood was the only one in the top-order to score at a strike rate of over 100.
Khalid Kail and Ayaan Khan stitched a 31-run partnership.
